data.enText: a person whose job is to decide how things such as clothes, furniture, tools, etc. will look or work by making drawings, plans or patterns

data.chText: 由著名设计师设计的；标有设计师姓名的；名牌的
data.enText: made by a famous designer ; expensive and having a famous brand name

data.chText: 他理了个时髦的发型，戴着一只耳环，还留着时髦的胡子楂。
data.enText: He had a trendy haircut, an earring and designer stubble (= a short beard, grown for two or three days and thought to look fashionable) .

tr: someone who creates plans to be used in making something (such as buildings)
a person who devises plots or intrigues
example: he is believed to be the principal designer of the terrorist bombing attack

tr: someone who specializes in graphic design
a person who specializes in designing architectural interiors and their furnishings

value.def: A designer is a person whose job is to design things by making drawings of them.

example.tran: 卡罗琳是一名时装设计师。

value.def: Designer clothes or designer labels are expensive, fashionable clothes made by a famous designer, rather than being made in large quantities in a factory.

example.ex: He wears designer clothes and drives an antique car...
example.tran: 他穿着著名设计师设计的服装，开着一部古董车。

example.ex: People want to buy designer labels for snob value.
example.tran: 人们想买名牌是为了满足虚荣心。

value.tran: (服装、品牌等)由著名设计师设计的，标有设计师姓名的

value.def: You can use designer to describe things that are worn or bought because they are fashionable.

example.ex: Tousled hair and designer stubble are chic...
example.tran: 乱蓬蓬的头发和时兴的胡茬都很新潮。

example.ex: Designer beers and trendy wines have replaced the good old British pint.
example.tran: 时尚的啤酒和流行的葡萄酒已经取代了老牌的英国啤酒。
